article.description: Utah Valley St. 66, N. Dakota St. 64
article.headline: Utah Valley St. 66, N. Dakota St. 64
article.linkText: Utah Valley St. 66, N. Dakota St. 64
article.story: OREM, Utah (AP) -- Ryan Toolson scored 20 points to lead Utah Valley State to a 66-64 win over North Dakota State on Thursday night. Toolson had eight points in the final three minutes during an 11-4 run that secured the win for the Wolverines (18-7). Ben Woodside led North Dakota State (15-8) with 24 points. Brett Winkleman scored 17, hitting a 3-pointer at the final buzzer. UVSC led by as many as 13 points early in the second half, but North Dakota State scored eight straight points to take a 57-55 lead with 3:30 left in the game. It was tied at 61 when Toolson hit a 3-pointer, then he added two free throws on the Wolverines' next possession to give Utah Valley State a 65-61 lead. Jordan Brady had seven points and 12 rebounds for UVSC.
